<TITLE> 6th Wage Board Award recommendations okayed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com)- The government Thursday approved the final recommendations of the Sixth Wage Board Award relating to salaries, allowances and other benefits for journalists, employees and press workers, the Press Information Department said in a statement. In 2005, a 13-member Wage Board was constituted with a retired judge of the Appellate Division as its chairman. The Sixth Wage Board submitted its recommendations to the government and accordingly, final recommendations have been approved. The information ministry has sent the recommendations to press for a gazette notification, the statement added.
